 upperparts and dull white underparts, faintly mottled with dusky brown. The call of this species is a nasal cherrrt or a rattle and roll, kert rrruk kert rrruk, and the melodious and complex song is a mix of clear whistles and musical trills. The banded wren forages actively in low vegetation or sometimes on the ground in pairs or family groups. It eats mainly eats insects, spiders and other invertebrates. References Mann, Nigel I.; Barker, F. Keith; Graves, Jeff A.; Dingess-Mann, Kimberly A. & Slater, Peter J. B. (2006): Molecular data delineate four genera of \"Thryothorus\" wrens. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 40: 750–759. doi:10.1016/j.ympev.2006.04.014 (HTML abstract) Stiles, F. Gary & Skutch, Alexander Frank (1989): A guide to the birds of Costa Rica. Comistock, Ithaca. ISBN 0-8014-9600-4 External links Research on the song", "shortSummary": "The banded wren (Thryophilus pleurostictus) is a small songbird of the wren family. It is a resident breeding species from central Mexico t…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6a/Banded_Wren_-_Chiapas_-_Mexico_S4E7334_%2817142375026%29.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-thryophilus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-thryophilus-pleurostictus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-thryophilus", "species": "taxonomy-species-thryophilus-pleurostictus"}, "expandable": true, "x": -407.74, "y": -219.56, "z": 362.88}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-thryophilus", "name": "Thryophilus", "latinName": "Thryophilus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Thryophilus（Thryophilus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联5种鸟类，如Sinaloa wren、Banded wren、Rufous-and-white wren等5种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 5, "x": -372.05, "y": 557.42, "z": 20.79}], "links": [{"key": "bird-banded-